Download the ‚Äúcereal.csv‚Äù data file (linked above), copy it to your Project folder, and read it into R as a tibble. Then create a pipeline to produce a short list of cereals for me to try. I am only interested in cold cereals with a rating greater than 70. Please arrange the list so that the cereals with the fewest calories are displayed at the top. Save the result as a tibble called jeffs_list (I expect it to be even more popular than Craig‚Äôs list üôÉ) and print it.



